Nothing makes any fucking sense anymore. All the greatest things in life aren't nearly as great as you think they are. Somehow I always seem to shit myself into ignoring the truth. Thank you for letting me down like this.

Well I can't regret, can't you just forget it? I started something I couldn't finish And if we go down, we go down together best friends means, well best friends means... And I've got a twenty-dollar bill that says you're up late night starting fist fights versus fences in your backyard Wearing your black eye like a badge of honor Soaking in sympathy from friends who never loved you nearly half as much as me... Broken down in bars and bathrooms All I did was what I had to Don't believe me when I tell you it's just what anyone would do Take the time to talk about it Think a lot and live without it Don't believe me when I tell you it's something unforgivable... Well I can't regret, can't you just forget it? I started something I couldn't finish If we go down, we go down together best friends means, well best friends means You never knew well I never told you... Everything I know about breaking hearts I learned from you, it's true I've never done it with the style and grace you have But I've made long term plans based on these mistakes Broken down in bars and bathrooms All I did was what I had to Don't believe me when I tell you it's just what anyone would do Take the time to talk about it Think a lot and live without it Don't believe me when I tell you it's something unforgivable Is this what you call tact? I swear you're as subtle as a brick in the small of my back so let's end this call, and end this conversation there's nothing worse... ...that's right he said, that's right he said it... ...have another drink and drive yourself home... I swear, you have no idea ...I hope there's ice on all the roads... The jealousy that became me thinking ...that's right he said... ...and you can think of me when you forget your seatbelt... that you always had it way too easy ...and again when your head goes through the windshield... Broken down in bars and bathrooms All I did was what I had to Don't believe me when I tell you it's just what anyone would do Take the time to talk about it Think a lot and live without it Don't believe me when I tell you it's something unforgivable Best friends means I pulled the trigger Best friends means you get what you deserve...

So...here is a brief undescriptive account of what is/has been going on with me lately. Warped Tour was simply amazing/wonderful/great/orgasmic. Perhaps I will post some pictures later on, if I get really motivated to do so. I just finished my end of summer mix cd. It's so amazing to listen to it and remember all the great memories I've made this summer. Perhaps I will post the track listing later on, if I get really motivated to do so.. heh. heh... I am taking American government this year, and I hate it with a passion. My father really freaks me out lately. Yeh.

Omigod. World peace. Omigod. Omigod, omigod, omigod...

I bought The Perks Of Being A Wallflower yesterday... I started reading it last night, and I'm almost done. So far, it's such an amazingly great book. I can relate it so much, and I think alot of other people can relate to it as well, even if they won't admit to it. I've also cried over this book a few times. Is that horrible or what? heh heh.. But, I would recommend this book to anyone. So go buy it or check it out from the library now...

Once on a yellow piece of paper with green lines he wrote a poem And he called it "Chops" because that was the name of his dog And that's what it was all about And his teacher gave him an A and a gold star And his mother hung it on the kitchen door and read it to his aunts That was the year Father Tracy took all the kids to the zoo And he let them sing on the bus And his little sister was born with tiny toenails and no hair And his mother and father kissed a lot And the girl around the corner sent him a Valentine signed with a row of X's and he had to ask his father what the X's meant And his father always tucked him in bed at night Once on a piece of white paper with blue lines he wrote a poem And he called it "Autumn" because that was the name of the season And that's what it was all about And his teacher gave him an A and asked him to write more clearly And his mother never hung it on the kitchen door because of its new paint And the kids told him that Father Tracy smoked cigars And left butts on the pews And sometimes they would burn holes That was the year his sister got glasses with thick lenses and black frames And the girl around the corner laughed when he asked her to go see Santa Claus And the kids told him why his mother and father kissed a lot And his father never tucked him in bed at night And his father got mad when he cried for him to do it. Once on a paper torn from his notebook he wrote a poem And he called it "Innocence:A Question" because that was the question about his girl And that's what it was all about And his professor gave him an A and a strange steady look And his mother never hung it on the kitchen door because he never showed her That was the year Father Tracy died And he forgot how the end of the Apostle's Creed went And he caught his sister making out on the back porch And his mother and father never kissed or even talked And the girl around the corner wore too much makeup That made him cough when he kissed her but he kissed her anyway because that was the thing to do And at three A.M. he tucked himself into bed his father was snoring soundly That's why on the back of a brown paper bag he tried another poem And he called it "Absolutely Nothing" Because that's what it was really all about And he gave himself an A And a slash on each damned wrist And he hung it on the bathroom door because this time he didn't think he could reach the kitchen.

So I just got back from my homeschool group's annual bake sale. I had way more fun today that anyone should ever have at a bake sale. Xenia came to 'help out the cause', so ofcourse we had an awesome time. We bought our traditional neon pink posterboard and made a sign, and stood by the road in the middle of Jasper holding the sign yelling "You're not too cool for cake!" at passing motorists. After doing that for about an hour we decided that we'd sell more stuff by walking/skating door to door. Jasper is not the best place to skate, and it's even more difficult when you're carrying around a huge basket of assorted baked goodies. We got to skate for a little while, but we mostly just took turns carrying the board around, but magaged to look uber cool in the process. heh. heh. We went to pretty much every store/business in town, and only made fourteen dollars. So after we we returned to the park, we went to Subway for lunch. The girl who made our sandwhiches asked me if I was in a band. Heh... After lunch we went to a few random thrift shops, but bought nothing. Then we went to the dollar store. There Xenia got some awesome undies with garter straps, and we both bought a pair of metal play handcuffs. ...All we needed was some whipped cream and a whip.. hmm... ;-) When we were walking back, we discoverd a shopping cart with a broken wheel in the alley behind Family Dollar. It looked like it could be alot of fun.. We took turns pushing eachother around in it, and waving to random people. We crashed once... We were laughing soo hard. "It was soo Jackass!" We got called immature by an eight-year-old. And had a blast on the merry-go-round. We walked to CVS and bought magazines, and then headed back to the park around 2:30, and headed home not long after... So in conclusion.... Today was a fun day.

Today was a good day. Nothing that special or exiting happened. It was just an all around good day. I'm just starting to realize that I'm happy with the way my life is right now, nomatter how confusing things may be. I just feel like something big is going to happen soon, and it will change things for the better. Maybe my hopes are too high. But I have this feeling that something good will happen in the near future. I don't really even understand why I feel this way now, since just last night I was so overwhelmed by everything. But today, I felt like a huge weight has been lifted off of me. I feel...great! Anyway. I got Copeland - In Motion today. It's such an amazing album. Simply beautiful. Go buy it. Now! And apparantly I'm the only kid in this area to get a copy of it, since Best Buy only got in one today, and Target and FYE didn't seem to have it either. I'm just special like that I guess. And I wouldn't have even gotten it today if it wasn't for my wonderful new friend Keysha at Best Buy digging it out of the storage room for me. Yay for making new friends! I also got Gratitude today. I havn't got a chance to listen to it yet, but I predict it will be amazingly awesome, since I have never heard any of Jonah Matranga's music that I didn't love. I got a ton of assorted dirt cheap discount body jewelry today, and a really neat black and white striped shirt. Yay! Well. That about sums it up. Goodnight kids....

I never thoguht I'd say this..but as much as I love rainy weather, I really am tired of it. It's been raining pretty much constantly for like a week now. Ughh... Anyway, not much of interest has been happening lately. I met a guy at the grocery store today when I was looking at the Easter candy. His name was Donovan. He said I was pretty. He's on a cross country hitchhiking adventure, and attending lots of jam band festivals. We talked about Cadburry Eggs, Reese's Peices, M&M's, hitchhiking, and many other interesting things. Donovan was a pretty interesting/neato guy. We hugged. It's too bad he didn't have a phone, or I would have totally gotten his number. I ate at Sonic for the first time ever today. Sonic is officially the greatest fast food place ever! I got a Lime Slush and a chicken club toaster sandwhich. Those Lime Slushes are the greatest thing since sliced bread. <font size=1><font face=arial>So... I went to the Stephen Foster Park in White Springs today, and I ate at the cafe where Xenia works. I got to hang out with her for a little while too. The food there is amazing. My pasta was served with a little yellow flower on it, and...I ate it. It tasted like spearment. How cool is that?  Ahhh...I love being easily amused.
I also went to the mall in Lake City today. That place is the crappiest excuse for a mall ever. It was mostly deserted, except for a few old people sitting in the chairs in the middle of the mall. They all stared at me blankly when I walked by. It was kind of scary.
I went in Sam Goody, and some hip-hop type clothing store. I bought nothing. *sigh*

So long and goodnight.

<font size=1><font face=arial>I got my hair cut today. It looks basicly the same as it did before. Only, slightly shorter, ofcourse. 
I called Ben after I got home. And then Xenia called to inform me that Green Day and My Chemical Romance are comming to Jacksonville, April 19th...!!!!!!

I am <u>so</u> there.

Eeeee!!!  :-D

I'm a happy kid right now.

(All of this was written on the 20th, but I just didn't get around to posting it until now...) The concert was a simply in-flippin-credible time. My throat still hurts from screaming, and my ears are still ringing. Amazing. :-D I'm not going to go into extreme detail about the concert, because it would take a really, really long time.. And I don't think anyone really wants to sit there for 40 minutes to read about it all. Sooo, anyway.... We got to Wild Aventures around 12:30. Around 1pm, Xenia and I headed over to the "Snow Days" area of the park (fake snow, from a snow machine, ofcourse) and we passed the concert stage, which was completly empty, except for maybe three other kids standing by the fence. And there we got to watch Bowling For Soup setting up. Then we played in the snow, while listening to BFS, and being chased by evil little kids who pelted us with snowballs. We made a five dollar bet on which band whould play first. I, ofcourse lost... The first to perform was MC Lars...who is simply amazing... He's a post-punk laptop rapper and the most original thing I've seen in a long long time. He raps about stuff like Edgar Allen Poe, and England. Everyone should check him out... We got to meet him after the show, he is such an amazingly nice guy. We got autographs, and chatted for like 10 minutes. We talked about college, the Waffle House, Florida, and many other interesting things. After MC Lars, it was Riddlin Kids, American Hi Fi, then BFS. They were all excellect. We also got to meet AHF and got their autographs. And Xenia got her RK shirt signed by the singer from the band. I asked every one of the band members what their favorite kind of pie and/or cake was. Good fun, indeed. After the concert we went back to my house, and watched large amounts of music videos, coppied lots of cds, and watched Napoleon Dynomite. Hooray.

So, ummm...Happy Valentine's Day. I hate Valentine's Day. It's rainy and, cold, and icky outside. It always seems to rain on Valentine's Day, why is that? Weird. The Valentine Bunny came to my bathroom this morning and left me a stuffed doggie, a box and candy, and a card... Hooray Valentine Bunny! :-D Man, banana sammiches and Yoo Hoo sure are good. I'm bored. I think I'm gona go take a nap... See ya later, Sweet potater!

I hung out with Steph alot. And I also got to hang out with Chris and Trey and all those people I hardly ever see anymore. There was lots of good food there as well. Lots of good sugary food. Yess,muahhhahahaa.... Cupcakes, brownies, red velvet cake, cookies of all kinds, etc... Sugary goodness. So awesome.

The Valentines's Day banquet is tomarrow. I'm not too exited about that. I don't want to go. At all. I was hoping I'd get to play guitar and sing, but that didn't work out.  I'll be singing with Paula though, and Steph will play piano. meh...
